# Todo App

A simple Todo application built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB.

## Features

- Add new todo tasks with title, description, priority, and due date.
- View all todo tasks.
- View a single todo task by its ID.
- Update an existing todo task.
- Delete a todo task.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository

2. Navigate to the project directory:  
   cd your-repository

3. Install dependencies:
   npm install

4. Set up environment variables (if any).

   - Connect to mongodb
     url=your_mongodb_connection_string
   - Replace `your_mongodb_connection_string` with your actual MongoDB connection string.

5. Use Postman interact with the API endpoints.

    - Using JSON insert values.

## API Endpoints

- `GET /todo`: Get all todos
- `POST /todo`: Create a new todo
- `GET /api/todos/:id`: Get a single todo by its ID
- `PUT /todo/:id`: Update a todo , example : localhost:3000/todo/66609abfb0bb8b85f4af2192
- `DELETE /todo/:id`: Delete a todo
